Dimocarpus longan var. malesianus

   [5350.jpg]
    Authority   Lour.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Sapindaceae
     Synonyms   Dimocarpus longan var. malesianus Leenh.
   Common names green longan
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5350

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A small to medium-sized tree usually reaching 10-20 m
   in height. The fruits are globular to slightly oblong and smooth to
   warty. USES The fruits are mainly eaten fresh. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES Mata kucing, Isau, Sau, Kakus, Buku, Ihau,
   Medaru. FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: Nephelium malaiense, Euphoria
   cinerea, E. malaiensis, E. gracilis. Mata kucing can be found all over
   Indo-China and Malesia, with the greatest variation in Borneo. It
   thrives in the humid tropical lowlands near sea level within the
   latitudinal range 10Â°N-S. It can be found in areas with a relative
   humidity from 65-95%. The tree mainly occurs in the understorey in
   primary or sometimes secondary forests.

   Sources
   Verheij E 1991 pp 146-151 [USE, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH]

